You are here: Salesforce Help > Docs > Insurance > Insurance Spring '23 Release Notes

Expedite financial authorization requests with a workflow that routes them directly to supervisors. Define user-specific attribute values with profile-based attribute rules. Backdate policy changes with out-of-sequence endorsement quoting. Delete census data for group benefits directly on the quote record page.

Automatic Upgrades
Starting in Spring '23, we're moving our Insurance managed package to the Salesforce automatic upgrade process.

Required Upgrade to OAuth 2.0 for DocuSign Integration in Insurance
For Vlocity Document Generation, you must upgrade to OAuth 2.0 to manage DocuSign.

Build Business Processes for Financial Transaction Authorizations
Set limits on how much users can authorize for claim payments and build a workflow that routes payment authorization requests to supervisors.

Apply Rules to Deeper Levels of the Product Hierarchy
We've improved the way insurance rules are evaluated for more complex insurance products.

Customize Attribute Values Based On User Profiles
Show users unique product attribute values based on their user profile.

Delete Census Members for a Group Benefits Quote
Use the Insurance Quote Census Lightning web component in the Salesforce data model to delete members on a Quote record page.

Issue an Out-of-Sequence Endorsement
Create endorsements for transactions that have an effective date prior to the effective date of another active transaction on the same policy.

Open Coverages Easily for More Policy Types
Enhancements simplify the open coverage process.

View Transaction Breakdown for an Insurance Policy Transaction
We've enhanced the Insurance Transaction Management to generate the transaction breakdowns for different payment frequencies and payment methods.

Services for Insurance Spring '23
Explore new services and updates to existing services in Spring '23.

Data Model Updates for Insurance Spring '23
Explore new and enhanced data model objects for this release.

Insurance Application Suite Spring '23 Release
These release notes provide details about the changes in the Spring '23 release of the Insurance Application Suite.
title: Insurance Spring '23 Release Notes
